{"name": "proxy-tools", "metadata": {"name": "proxy_tools", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": ["Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "http://github.com/jtushman/proxy_tools", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Proxy Implementation", "upload_time": 1399323744}, "documentation": ["---\nsubstitutions:\n  Build Status: |-\n    ```{image} https://travis-ci.org/jtushman/proxy.svg?branch=master\n    :target: https://travis-ci.org/jtushman/proxy_tools\n    ```\n---\n\n# proxy_tools\n\nI'm just a proxy\n\n{{ Build Status }}\n\nLoveingly extracted from [werkzeug]. A very useful proxy implementation, that I found to be useful outside\nthe web context -- hence the extraction.\n\n## Install\n\n```bash\npip install proxy\n```\n\n## Basic Usage\n\n```python\nfrom proxy_tools import Proxy\np = Proxy()\n\ndef get_current_user():\n    return User.find_by_id(request['user_id'])\n\ncurrent_user = p(get_current_user)\n\n# Or alternatively\n\nfrom proxy_tools import module_property\n\n@module_property\ndef current_user():\n    return User.find_by_id(request['user_id'])\n\n# Then\nprint(current_user.name)\n```\n\n## Questions / Issues\n\nFeel free to ping me on twitter: [@tushman]\nor add issues or PRs at <https://github.com/jtushman/proxy_tools>\n\n## Thank you\n\nTo Armin Ronacher and the [werkzeug] team for their thought leadership and excellent work\n\n[@tushman]: http://twitter.com/tushman\n[werkzeug]: https://github.com/mitsuhiko/werkzeug\n"], "modules": [{"name": "setup", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "setup.required_modules", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.packages", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "proxy_tools", "documentation": ["proxy_tools.py\n~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\n\nProxy. Extracted from Werkzeug\n\n:cop